# What is an Intrusion Prevention System (IPS)?

An **Intrusion Prevention System (IPS)** is a network security tool that monitors network traffic and actively blocks malicious activities.

Unlike an **Intrusion Detection System (IDS)**, which only generates alerts, an IPS can prevent attacks by blocking harmful traffic before it reaches the network.

---

# About Snort

**Snort** is one of the most widely used open-source network security tools. It performs:

* Real-time traffic monitoring
* Packet logging
* Intrusion detection
* Intrusion prevention
* Attack signature detection

Snort can operate in both **IDS mode and IPS mode**.

