# Installation & Setup

The following commands were used to install and configure Snort on the Linux system.

```bash
# Update system packages
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade

# Install Snort
sudo apt install snort -y

# Verify Snort installation
snort -V

# Identify network interfaces
ip a

# Run Snort in IDS mode
sudo snort -A console -q -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -i eth0
```

During installation, Snort requires configuration of the **HOME_NET**, which represents the local network.

Example:

```
192.168.1.0/24
```

---

# Snort Configuration

The main configuration file of Snort is:

```
/etc/snort/snort.conf
```

Open the configuration file using:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/snort/snort.conf
```

Set the local network variable:

```
ipvar HOME_NET 192.168.1.0/24
```

---

# Custom Rule Creation

Local rules can be added in the following file:

```
/etc/snort/rules/local.rules
```

Example rule used to detect ICMP ping traffic:

```
alert icmp any any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"Ping Detected"; sid:1000001; rev:1;)
```

This rule generates an alert whenever ping traffic is detected in the network.

